White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki spoke at the James S. Brady Press Briefing Room about various topics, including President Biden's upcoming trip to Illinois to meet with leaders who have implemented vaccination requirements, the ongoing debt ceiling negotiations, the Uyghur Forced Labor Prevention Act, the possibility of a virtual summit between President Biden and President Xi of China, energy prices, school shootings, Facebook's role in spreading misinformation, and the administration's stance on voting rights and the Black agenda. Psaki also discussed the recent oil spill in California and the administration's efforts to address it, as well as the availability and affordability of rapid COVID-19 tests.